.TH "TEMPORAL.PLAINDATE.YEAROFWEEK" "3JS" "December 8, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
Temporal.PlainDate.yearOfWeek \- Temporal.PlainDate.prototype.yearOfWeek
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]yearOfWeek\f[B]\f[R] accessor property of
\f[CR]Temporal.PlainDate\f[R] instances returns an integer representing
the year to be paired with the \f[CR]weekOfYear\f[R] of this date, or
\f[CR]undefined\f[R] if the calendar does not have a well\-defined week
system.
It is calendar\-dependent.
.PP
Usually this is the year of the date, but for ISO 8601, the first and
last few days of the year may be attributed to the last week of the
previous year or the first week of the next year, causing the
\f[CR]yearOfWeek\f[R] to differ by 1.
See \f[CR]weekOfYear\f[R] for more details.
.PP
The set accessor of \f[CR]yearOfWeek\f[R] is \f[CR]undefined\f[R].
You cannot change this property directly.
.SH EXAMPLES
See the examples in the \f[CR]weekOfYear\f[R] page.
